          "title": "NVIDIA garak Tutorial: Build a Complete Defensive LLM Red-Teaming Workflow with Custom Probes and Detectors",
          "link": "https://www.marktechpost.com/2026/06/06/nvidia-garak-tutorial-build-a-complete-defensive-llm-red-teaming-workflow-with-custom-probes-and-detectors/",
          "id": "https://www.marktechpost.com/?p=80357",
          "publishedAt": "2026-06-07T05:11:09.000Z",
          "author": "Sana Hassan",
          "summary": "<p>This tutorial walks through NVIDIA garak as an end-to-end framework for defensive LLM red-teaming. It covers setup, plugin discovery, dry runs, real-model scans on a Hugging Face generator, and multi-probe evaluations. The workflow then analyzes safety scores and attack success rates, inspects flagged outputs, and extends garak with a custom probe and detector. It closes by exporting results in AVID format for structured vulnerability</p> <p>The post <a href=\"https://www.marktechpost.com/2026/06/06/nvidia-garak-tutorial-build-a-complete-defensive-llm-red-teaming-workflow-with-custom-probes-and-detectors/\">NVIDIA garak Tutorial: Build a Complete Defensive LLM Red-Teaming Workflow with Custom Probes and Detectors</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.marktechpost.com\">MarkTechPost</a>.</p>",
